    \'95    The Risk: When you mix a strong oxidant (ClO\uc0\u8322 ) directly with DMSO, they neutralize each other through an exothermic chemical reaction. This reaction can significantly reduce the structural potency of both compounds before they even pass through your skin, and it creates a localized chemical byproduct that can cause deep dermal irritation or inflammation.\
